<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFD2FFF8FF6BF9E5FD8FFD23" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD2FFF8FF6BF9E5FD91FEA3" blockId="8.[151,1127,1539,1626]" lastBlockId="9.[113,1090,220,723]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FF6BF9E5FEB8F9AA" bold="true" box="[151,262,1539,1562]" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FEF2F9E5FE76F9AA" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[270,456,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FEF2F9E5FE76F9AA" box="[270,456,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">Cassida catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the commonest species in SE Asia, distributed from continental 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFD2FFF9FEEDF9C5FECCF98A" box="[273,370,1571,1594]" name="Malaysia" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
to Sumba (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD2FFF9FE19F9C5FC87F98A" author="BOROWIEC &amp; SWIETOJANSKA" box="[485,825,1571,1594]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" refId="ref48617" refString="BOROWIEC L. &amp; SWIETOJANSKA J. 2016: Cassidinae of the world - an interactive manual (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Permanent electronic publication available from: http: // culex. biol. uni. wroc. pl / cassidae / katalog % 20 internetowy / index. htm (last accessed on 18 th May 2016)." type="url" year="2016">BOROWIEC &amp; ŚWIĘTOJAŃSKA 2016</bibRefCitation>
). It has a very variable colour pattern, ranging from a uniformly yellow dorsum to a primarily black discs of pronotum and elytra. The typical form has the disc of elytra black with numerous yellow spots and the disc of pronotum black with two yellow spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD3FFF8FF6CFEFAFD38FD83" blockId="9.[113,1090,220,723]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD3FFF8FF6CFEFAFEFEFE83" author="BOHEMAN" box="[144,320,284,307]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
also described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FE1CFEFAFDEAFE83" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[480,596,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FE1CFEFAFDEAFE83" box="[480,596,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">C. dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="2D12B0D4FFD3FFF8FD6EFEFAFD7AFE83" box="[658,708,284,307]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Java</collectingRegion>
, from the collection of Westermann. This taxon remained unknown to subsequent workers and was listed only in catalogues (see 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD3FFF8FF8DFEBAFE99FEC3" author="BOROWIEC" box="[113,295,348,371]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
). The original 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFD3FFF8FE38FEBAFE4CFEC3" box="[452,498,348,371]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">type</typeStatus>
specimen was located in ZMUC, where Westermann’s collection is housed. In my opinion this taxon represents a black form of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FC73FE9AFBB5FE23" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[911,1035,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FC73FE9AFBB5FE23" box="[911,1035,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">C. catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it differs from the latter only in colouration. Since both taxa were described in the same publication I followed the Principle of the first reviser (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD3FFF8FD6BFE5AFCA9FE63" author="ICZN" box="[663,791,444,467]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" refId="ref49784" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 24.2) and chose the name 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FF4CFE3AFE96FE43" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[176,296,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FF4CFE3AFE96FE43" box="[176,296,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">C. catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid, since it has been mentioned in numerous publications and is mostly correctly applied. The black form of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FDFAFE1AFD3DFDA3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[518,643,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FDFAFE1AFD3DFDA3" box="[518,643,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">C. catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also described as 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FC82FE1AFF0CFD83" authority="(Spaeth 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrari">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FC82FE1AFC58FDA3" box="[894,998,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">C. ferrari</emphasis>
(Spaeth 1904)
</taxonomicName>
, already synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD3FFF8FE34FDFAFD3CFD83" author="BOROWIEC" box="[456,642,540,563]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" pagination="493 - 562" refId="ref48341" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2001: New records of Asian and Australopapuan Cassidinae, with a description of five new species of Cassida from Thailand (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 12: 493 - 562." type="journal article" year="2001">BOROWIEC (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD3FFF8FF6CFDDAFD8FFD23" blockId="9.[113,1090,220,723]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD3FFF8FF6CFDDAFEF7FDE3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[144,329,572,595]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FF6CFDDAFEF7FDE3" box="[144,329,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Cassida catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also recorded from the southern foothills of the Eastern Himalaya (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD3FFF8FF54FDBAFE84FDC3" author="MAULIK" box="[168,314,604,627]" firstAuthor="MAULIK" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" refId="ref49986" refString="MAULIK S. 1919: Coleoptera. Chrysomelidae (Cassidinae and Hispinae). In: SHIPLEY A. E. (ed.): The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London, xi + 439 pp." type="book" year="1919">MAULIK 1919</bibRefCitation>
), however, that population is probably a distinct taxon and was thus not included in the distribution of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFD3FFF8FF8DFD7AFE05FD63" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD3FFF8FF8DFD7AFE05FD63" blockId="9.[113,1090,220,723]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD3FFF8FF8DFD7AFEBAFD03" bold="true" box="[113,260,668,691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFD3FFF8FEF6FD7AFECCFD03" box="[266,370,668,691]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(eastwards to Sumba) and 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFD3FFF8FD6DFD7AFD4DFD03" box="[657,755,668,691]" name="Malaysia" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(peninsular and 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFD3FFF8FC59FD7AFBBDFD03" box="[933,1027,668,691]" name="Malaysia" pageId="9" pageNumber="284">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
) (BOROWIEC &amp; ŚWIĘTOJAŃSKA 2016).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
